{
  "stem": "9168.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I'm relating this story to give you an idea of awareness of what was going on-- my awareness.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I spent that weekend in her parents' apartment in Chicago.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She told me-- she spoke very beautiful English.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "She told me that her parents did not speak English, and that she would interpret any conversation that we had between us, which would be, obviously, very minimal.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She showed me pictures of her growing up in Germany with all of her friends, who were in Nazi uniforms.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And some pictures, she had cut off the bottom part from the shoulder down, because she said that she did not want to have these pictures of her friends with Nazi uniforms on.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "The youth-- the-- the young group in Germany--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Nazi Youth, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was another name for them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I thought that was kind of interesting.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I knew she-- We didn't talk much about her life in Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But while I was in her-- their apartment that weekend, the radio was on, and Hitler had some great something.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I cannot attribute it to any of his marches into Poland, which was 1939.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was 1943-- '43 when I was in [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Graig ?] College before I went to Detroit.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But whatever it was, it was a huge quote, 'victory,' unquote, for Hitler.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Those two parents were so excited and happy for people who did not understand English.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I thought, there is something strange here going on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it wasn't until I got to Nuremberg-- she was the first person that I saw in the Grand Hotel, or in the courthouse-- courthouse when I arrived.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She had gotten back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "She was a US citizen then, as a court reporter.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
